    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-curry-pie-with-mustardy-greens/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to caramelise</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-curry-pie-with-mustardy-greens/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dust your work surface with a sprinkling of <strong>flour</strong>, then unwrap the<strong> puff pastry </strong>and roll it out to approx. 0.5cm thickness with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> and cut into 1 piece per person</p><p>Transfer the pastry to a <strong>non-stick baking paper</strong> lined-tray (or two!) and score a 1cm border around the edge of the pastry with a knife, then crimp the borders with a fork</p><p>Sprinkle your <strong>black sesame</strong> <strong>seeds</strong> over the pastry and put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until golden and cooked through \u2013 this is your<strong> pie lid[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-curry-pie-with-mustardy-greens/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has caramelised, add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong> and 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until fragrant</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve your<strong> tomato paste</strong> and<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-curry-pie-with-mustardy-greens/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>stock</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for 15 min or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p><p>Whilst the potatoes are cooking, wash your <strong>spring greens </strong>then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Rip the leaves off the <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-curry-pie-with-mustardy-greens/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate, large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> mustard seeds </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant and starting to pop</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced spring greens </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a slight bite \u2013 these are your <strong>mustardy greens</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-curry-pie-with-mustardy-greens/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>basa fillet[s] </strong>into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Place the<strong> chopped basa </strong>over the curry and cook, covered, for 4-5 min or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/basa-curry-pie-with-mustardy-greens/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>To serve, lay the <strong>pie lid</strong> over the <strong>basa</strong> <strong>curry pie filling</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>basa curry pie</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>basa curry pie</strong> with the <strong>mustardy greens</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
